Serves 2 but just adjust fish quantity to suit
/////
Crumb:
    Finely finely dice:
          A few sprigs of parsley
          The leaves of 1 very small sprig rosemary
          Other fresh herbs (dill, oregano, marjoram)
          2* cloves garlic (minced)
          Red chilli    
    Add the following and mix:
          Finely grated parmesan (about 5 tablespoons)
          1 cup breadcrumbs
          Zest of a lemon
          50mL or so olive oil
          Salt and pepper
/////
Fish:
    Heat oven to 200 degrees celcius
    Place 400g flathead fillets in a baking tray lined with baking paper
    Cover the fish with the crumb
    Bake for 15-20 minutes (crumb should be a bit crunchy on top)
